# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Type must be one of:
# - feat     (new feature)
# - fix      (bug fix)
# - docs     (documentation changes)
# - style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
# - refactor (refactoring production code)
# - test     (adding tests, refactoring test; no production code change)
# - chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
# - perf     (performance improvements)
# - ci       (CI/CD pipeline changes)
# - build    (build system changes)
# - revert   (revert previous commit)
#
# Scope is optional and should be the area of the codebase affected:
# - auth, stk, c2b, b2c, b2b, balance, reversal, config, docs, tests, etc.
#
# Description should be imperative mood, present tense, lowercase, no period
# Good: "add STK push timeout configuration"
# Bad: "Added STK push timeout configuration."
#
# Examples:
# feat(stk): add timeout configuration for STK push requests
# fix(auth): resolve token caching issue in production
# docs: update configuration guide with profile examples
# refactor(config): implement profile-based credential system
# test(stk): add comprehensive STK push validation tests
# chore(deps): update Laravel framework to version 11
#
# --- COMMIT END ---
# Remember to:
# - Keep the first line under 50 characters
# - Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
# - Can use multiple lines to explain complex changes
# - Reference issues and pull requests at the end
#
# Body (optional - leave blank line after subject):
#
#
# Footer (optional - reference issues):
# Fixes #123
# Closes #456
# Related to #789
